>>>>>>>>>>>>Angular JS directives

Angular js facilitates you to extend HTML with new attributes.
These attributes are called directives.

This is a set of Built in directive in Angular js, which offers functionality to your application. You can also define your own directives.

Directors are special attributes Starting with ng - prefix.
Following are the most common directives :

ngIf, ngFor, ngSwitch, ngClass etc...

*ng-app :These directors starts the Angular JS application.

*ng-init :This directive initializes application data.

*ng-model :This directive defends the model that is variable to be used in Angular JS

*ng-repeat :
This directive repeats a block of code for each element present inside an array or object.In other words, this directive repeats html elements for each item in a collection.
